<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62abbac3-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s2807"><num value="2807">§ 2807.</num><heading> Uniform allowance</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding the limitation in <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s5901/a">section 5901(a) of title 5</ref>, the Secretary may provide a uniform allowance for uniformed law enforcement officers under <ref href="/us/usc/t25/s2803">section 2803 of this title</ref> of not more than $400 a year.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id62abbac4-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/379/s8">Pub. L. 101–379, § 8</ref>, <date date="1990-08-18">Aug. 18, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/477">104 Stat. 477</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
